[
    {
        "text": "“My name’s Todd\nDouglas Miller.",
        "start": 0.5,
        "duration": 1.37
    },
    {
        "text": "I’m the director\nof “Apollo 11.”",
        "start": 1.87,
        "duration": 2.76
    },
    {
        "text": "So this is a very important\nscene in the film.",
        "start": 4.63,
        "duration": 2.76
    },
    {
        "text": "It’s the moment\non July 20, 1969,",
        "start": 7.39,
        "duration": 3.03
    },
    {
        "text": "the landing of Apollo 11.",
        "start": 10.42,
        "duration": 1.89
    },
    {
        "text": "This was the first time\nthat humanity set foot",
        "start": 12.31,
        "duration": 2.49
    },
    {
        "text": "on another world.",
        "start": 14.8,
        "duration": 1.17
    },
    {
        "text": "We spent a lot of\ntime on this scene.",
        "start": 15.97,
        "duration": 1.95
    },
    {
        "text": "It’s really the culmination\nof everyone’s talents,",
        "start": 17.92,
        "duration": 3.03
    },
    {
        "text": "from the sound design to\nMatt Morton’s music score.",
        "start": 20.95,
        "duration": 5.16
    },
    {
        "text": "Even to this animation,\nwhich was something",
        "start": 26.11,
        "duration": 2.91
    },
    {
        "text": "we decided to utilize,\nwhich is traditional cell",
        "start": 29.02,
        "duration": 2.79
    },
    {
        "text": "animation.",
        "start": 31.81,
        "duration": 0.78
    },
    {
        "text": "We came across that in\nsome industrial films",
        "start": 32.59,
        "duration": 2.49
    },
    {
        "text": "in NASA’s archives.”",
        "start": 35.08,
        "duration": 1.38
    },
    {
        "text": "— from which point the powered",
        "start": 36.46,
        "duration": 2.25
    },
    {
        "text": "descent to the lunar\nsurface will be initiated.”",
        "start": 38.71,
        "duration": 3.457
    },
    {
        "text": "“Apollo 11.",
        "start": 42.167,
        "duration": 1.003
    },
    {
        "text": "Houston, we are go\nfor undocking, over.”",
        "start": 43.17,
        "duration": 2.59
    },
    {
        "text": "“The landing itself\nwas obviously",
        "start": 45.76,
        "duration": 2.61
    },
    {
        "text": "a giant technical hurdle.",
        "start": 48.37,
        "duration": 1.56
    },
    {
        "text": "It involved hundreds\nof thousands of people,",
        "start": 49.93,
        "duration": 2.28
    },
    {
        "text": "but certainly, here, the\ndoors in mission control",
        "start": 52.21,
        "duration": 3.54
    },
    {
        "text": "are closed.",
        "start": 55.75,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "The three astronauts\nperforming",
        "start": 57.25,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "these complex maneuvers\nwere very much",
        "start": 58.75,
        "duration": 2.61
    },
    {
        "text": "focused on the task at hand.",
        "start": 61.36,
        "duration": 2.01
    },
    {
        "text": "One of the things that\nwe chose to utilize,",
        "start": 63.37,
        "duration": 2.305
    },
    {
        "text": "not only here, but\nthroughout the film,",
        "start": 65.675,
        "duration": 1.625
    },
    {
        "text": "was the use of split screens.",
        "start": 67.3,
        "duration": 1.71
    },
    {
        "text": "Here, for the first time, the\ntwo vehicles are separated,",
        "start": 69.01,
        "duration": 3.24
    },
    {
        "text": "Neil Armstrong and Buzz\nAldrin being on the right,",
        "start": 72.25,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "and Michael Collins in the\ncommand module on the left.",
        "start": 74.47,
        "duration": 3.21
    },
    {
        "text": "As we shift back\ninto mission control,",
        "start": 77.68,
        "duration": 1.86
    },
    {
        "text": "we always thought it was\nvery important to showcase",
        "start": 79.54,
        "duration": 3.84
    },
    {
        "text": "as many flight controllers\ninterjecting as much humanity",
        "start": 83.38,
        "duration": 5.49
    },
    {
        "text": "on screen as possible.",
        "start": 88.87,
        "duration": 2.17
    },
    {
        "text": "So when we have\nthese go,",
        "start": 91.04,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "no go commands — “",
        "start": 92.56,
        "duration": 1.247
    },
    {
        "text": "“Go.”",
        "start": 93.807,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "“GUIDO.”",
        "start": 94.307,
        "duration": 0.383
    },
    {
        "text": "“Go.”",
        "start": 94.69,
        "duration": 0.447
    },
    {
        "text": "“Guidance.”",
        "start": 95.137,
        "duration": 0.383
    },
    {
        "text": "“Go.”",
        "start": 95.52,
        "duration": 0.49
    },
    {
        "text": "“Control.”",
        "start": 96.01,
        "duration": 0.42
    },
    {
        "text": "“Go.”",
        "start": 96.43,
        "duration": 0.47
    },
    {
        "text": "“Telcom”",
        "start": 96.9,
        "duration": 0.42
    },
    {
        "text": "“Go.”",
        "start": 97.32,
        "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
        "text": "“GNC.”",
        "start": 97.82,
        "duration": 0.565
    },
    {
        "text": "“Go.”",
        "start": 98.385,
        "duration": 0.282
    },
    {
        "text": "“EECOM.”",
        "start": 98.667,
        "duration": 0.383
    },
    {
        "text": "“Go.”",
        "start": 99.05,
        "duration": 0.447
    },
    {
        "text": "“Surgeon.”",
        "start": 99.497,
        "duration": 0.383
    },
    {
        "text": "“Go.”",
        "start": 99.88,
        "duration": 0.39
    },
    {
        "text": "“CAPCOM — “",
        "start": 100.27,
        "duration": 0.6
    },
    {
        "text": "“These individuals were\npushing the buttons",
        "start": 100.87,
        "duration": 2.05
    },
    {
        "text": "to make these things\nhappen, and we always",
        "start": 102.92,
        "duration": 2.96
    },
    {
        "text": "thought that it would\nbe important to showcase",
        "start": 105.88,
        "duration": 2.28
    },
    {
        "text": "as much of these\npeople as we could.",
        "start": 108.16,
        "duration": 4.11
    },
    {
        "text": "The on-screen graphics, we\nspent a lot of time working",
        "start": 112.27,
        "duration": 3.66
    },
    {
        "text": "with the historians — \nand also the astronauts,",
        "start": 115.93,
        "duration": 2.22
    },
    {
        "text": "both Michael Collins\nand Buzz Aldrin —",
        "start": 118.15,
        "duration": 2.01
    },
    {
        "text": "to get that as accurate\nas we possibly could.",
        "start": 120.16,
        "duration": 2.85
    },
    {
        "text": "Neil’s sons Rick and Mark\nalso contributed a lot",
        "start": 123.01,
        "duration": 3.33
    },
    {
        "text": "to the making of the film.",
        "start": 126.34,
        "duration": 1.47
    },
    {
        "text": "And then this is one of\nthe most famous shots",
        "start": 127.81,
        "duration": 2.55
    },
    {
        "text": "in cinematic history,\nas far as I’m concerned.",
        "start": 130.36,
        "duration": 1.98
    },
    {
        "text": "Buzz Aldrin shot this with\na 16-millimeter camera",
        "start": 132.34,
        "duration": 3.42
    },
    {
        "text": "out his window, and\nthen we in the film",
        "start": 135.76,
        "duration": 3.54
    },
    {
        "text": "show it as an unbroken shot\nto the moment of touchdown.",
        "start": 139.3,
        "duration": 4.18
    },
    {
        "text": "My music composer,\nMatt Morton,",
        "start": 143.48,
        "duration": 2.3
    },
    {
        "text": "decided to do a period score\nusing only instrumentation",
        "start": 145.78,
        "duration": 3.9
    },
    {
        "text": "that was around pre-1969.",
        "start": 149.68,
        "duration": 2.07
    },
    {
        "text": "Most notably, he went out\nand got a 1968 edition Moog",
        "start": 151.75,
        "duration": 3.72
    },
    {
        "text": "synthesizer.”",
        "start": 155.47,
        "duration": 0.6
    },
    {
        "text": "[tense music]",
        "start": 156.07,
        "duration": 2.75
    }
]